# aegis-plugin-{{ name }}

{{ description }}

An [Aegis Stack](https://github.com/lbedner/aegis-stack) plugin.

## Install

```bash
pip install aegis-plugin-{{ name }}
```

Or for local development:

```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Use

Inside an Aegis Stack project:

```bash
aegis add {{ name }}
```

That will:
- Append a `_plugins` entry to your project's `.copier-answers.yml`
- Render any templates this plugin ships under `src/aegis_plugin_{{ name }}/templates/{% raw %}{{ project_slug }}/{% endraw %}` into your project tree
- Regenerate aegis-stack shared files so the plugin's wiring (routers, deps,
  cards, etc.) takes effect

## Layout

```
aegis-plugin-{{ name }}/
├── pyproject.toml
├── src/aegis_plugin_{{ name }}/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── plugin.py                 ← exposes get_spec() (the entry point)
│   └── templates/
│       └── {% raw %}{{ project_slug }}/{% endraw %}      ← files this plugin drops into the target project
└── tests/
    └── test_plugin.py
```

## Develop

```bash
make install     # uv sync
make test        # pytest
make check       # lint + test
make fix         # ruff format + autofix
```

